commit.message: Fix Python 2 compatibility
Fix default marker import name
Remove test after default behavior changed (literal false)

Use a module rather than a class (since it's not callable)

Some expression compiler implementation use duck-typing to check whether
a default marker is callable and would attempt to do so if it was.

Default marker should be an importable symbol

This is useful for integrations which might need to return a
value of <default> rather than a computed value.
Unused node class

Default should be a global object

commit.message:
Default should be a global object

Note that we use 'intern' here to assert that the string will
indeed be interned (and become a global), but also to prevent
Python from complaining that we're abusing object identity with
strings (which is discouraged in Python 3.8).

This problem may be solved differently in a future release.
Version bump
